methods.name: Derivation Method for ASTDT
methods.description: AE.AESTDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date. Some events with partial dates are imputed in a conservative manner. If the day component is missing, a value of '01' is used. If both the month and day are missing no imputation is performed as these dates clearly indicate a start prior to the beginning of treatment. There are no events with completely missing start dates.

methods.name: Derivation Method for ASTDTF
methods.description: ASTDTF='D' if the day value within the character date is imputed. Note that only day values needed to be imputed for this study.

methods.name: Derivation Method for ASTDY
methods.description: IF ASTDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>ASTDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT

methods.name: Derivation Method for AENDT
methods.description: AE.AEENDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date

methods.name: Derivation Method for AENDY
methods.description: IF AENDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>AENDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT

methods.name: Derivation Method for ADURU
methods.description: If ADURN is not missing then ADURU='DAY'

methods.name: Derivation Method for TRTEMFL
methods.description: If ASTDT >= TRTSDT > . then TRTEMFL='Y'. Otherwise TRTEMFL='N'

methods.name: Derivation Method for AOCCFL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCFL=Y) within each Subject

methods.name: Derivation Method for AOCCSFL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCSFL=Y) within each Subject and SOC

methods.name: Derivation Method for AOCCPFL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCPFL=Y) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

methods.name: Derivation Method for AOCC02FL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC02FL=Y) within each Subject

methods.name: Derivation Method for AOCC03FL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC03FL=Y) within each Subject and SOC

methods.name: Derivation Method for AOCC04FL
methods.description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC04FL=Y) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

methods.name: Derivation Method for CQ01NAM
methods.description: If AEDECOD contains any of the character strings of ('APPLICATION', 'DERMATITIS', 'ERYTHEMA', 'BLISTER') OR if AEBODSYS='SKIN AND SUBC UTANEOUS TISSUE DISORDERS' but AEDECOD is not in ('COLD SWEAT', 'HYPERHIDROSIS', 'ALOPECIA') then CQ01NAM='DERMATOLOGIC EVENTS' Otherwise CQ01NAM=NULL

methods.name: Derivation Method for AOCC01FL
methods.description: Subset to CQ01NAM='' and TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC01FL=Y) within each Subject (Flag First Treatment Emergent Dermatological Event for Time to Event Analysis)

methods.name: Derivation Method for PARAM
methods.description: For PARAMN<100: same as LB.LBTEST concatenated with LB.LBSTRESU. For PARAMN>100: LB.LBTEST concatenated with LB.LBSTRESU concatenated with " change from previous visit, relative to normal range"

methods.name: Derivation Method for PARAMCD
methods.description: For PARAMN<100: same as LBTESTCD, For PARAMN>100: _ + LBTESTCD

methods.name: Derivation Method for ALBTRVAL
methods.description: Maximum of [LBSTRESN-(1.5*ULN)] and [(.5*LLN) - LBSTRESN]

methods.name: Derivation Method for AENTMTFL
methods.description: Last observed value for this lab parameter during treatment phase: 'Y' if VISITNUM=12, if subject discontinues prior to VISIT 12, then this variable is set to 'Y' if this is the last assessment of this analyte for the subject

methods.name: Derivation Method for PARAM
methods.description: For PARAMN<100: same as LBTEST concatenated with LBSTRESU For PARAMN>100: LBTEST concatenated with LB.LBSTRESU concatenated with "change from previous visit, relative to normal range"

methods.name: Derivation Method for PARAMCD
methods.description: For PARAMN<100: same as LBTESTCD For PARAMN>100: _ + LBTESTCD

methods.name: Derivation Method for AENTMTFL
methods.description: Last observed value for this lab test during treatment phase: 'Y' if VISITNUM=12, if subject discontinues prior to VISIT 12, then this variable is set to 'Y' if this is the last assessment of this analyte for the subject

methods.name: Derivation Method for PARAM
methods.description: same as LBTEST concatenated with LBSTRESU except for hylaw params

methods.name: Derivation Method for AVISIT
methods.description: Derived based on windowing algorithm described in SAP, Section 8.2

methods.name: Derivation Method for ADY
methods.description: ADY = ADT - TRTSDT + 1, if ADT>=TRTSDT. ADY = ADT - TRTSDT, if ADT<TRTSDT.

methods.name: Derivation Method for PARAMN
methods.description: Assign a numeric code for each value of PARAMCD (see codelistPARAMN_ADQSADAS)

methods.name: Derivation Method for BASE
methods.description: QS.QSSTRESN when QS.QSBLFL=Y (QS.VISITNUM=3)

methods.name: Derivation Method for ANL01FL
methods.description: If multiple visits fall into the same visit window, then the one closest to the target date is chosen for analysis. These are flagged with ANL01FL="Y".

methods.name: Derivation Method for AWRANGE
methods.description: Window range, specified in the SAP.

methods.name: Derivation Method for AWTARGET
methods.description: Target day within the window, specified in the SAP.

methods.name: Derivation Method for AWTDIFF
methods.description: Absolute difference between AWTARGET and ADY

methods.name: Derivation Method for AWLO
methods.description: Start day of the window, specified in the SAP.

methods.name: Derivation Method for AWHI
methods.description: End day of the window, specified in the SAP.

methods.name: Derivation Method for AVISIT
methods.description: Character version of the visit.

methods.name: Derivation Method for AVISITN
methods.description: Using window method in SAP Page 10 to determine AVISITN value based on ADY.

methods.name: Derivation Method for AVAL
methods.description: QS.QSSTRESN, where QS.QSTESTCD = CIBIC

methods.name: Derivation Method for ANL01FL
methods.description: Set ANL01FL=Y based on SAP Page 10 analysis windows.

methods.name: Derivation Method for DTYPE
methods.description: Value: LOCF denotes that the LOCF imputation method was used to impute the value for the given parameter and analysis visit.

methods.name: Derivation Method for PARAMN
methods.description: Assign a numeric code for each value of PARAMCD (see codelist PRMNNPIX)

methods.name: Derivation Method for AWRANGE
methods.description: Window range, specified in the SAP Page 10.

methods.name: Derivation Method for AWTARGET
methods.description: Target day within the window, specified in the SAP Page 10.

methods.name: Derivation Method for AWLO
methods.description: Start day of the window, specified in the SAP Page 10.

methods.name: Derivation Method for AWHI
methods.description: End day of the window, specified in the SAP Page 10.

methods.name: Derivation Method for SITEGR1
methods.description: refer to SAP, Section 7.1 - if not pooled then SITEGR1=SITEID. If pooled, SITEGR1 will be 900

methods.name: Derivation Method for TRT01PN
methods.description: Numeric code for TRT01P which corresponds to the randomized dose

methods.name: Derivation Method for TRT01A
methods.description: TRT01A=TRT01P, i.e., no difference between actual and randomized treatment in this study.

methods.name: Derivation Method for TRT01AN
methods.description: Numeric code for TRT01A which corresponds to the randomized dose

methods.name: Derivation Method for TRTSDT
methods.description: SV.SVSTDTC when SV.VISITNUM=3, converted to SAS date

methods.name: Derivation Method for TRTEDT
methods.description: The date of final dose (from the CRF) is EX.EXENDTC on the subject's last EX record. If the date of final dose is missing for the subject and the subject discontinued after visit 3, use the date of discontinuation as the date of last dose. Convert the date to a SAS date.

methods.name: Derivation Method for CUMDOSE
methods.description: For ARMN=0 or 1: CUMDOSE=TRT01PN*TRTDUR. --- For ARMN=2: CUMDOSE will be based on 54mg per day for the # of days subj was in 1st dosing interval (i.e., visit4date-TRTSTDT+1 if 1st interval completed, TRTEDT-TRTSTDT+1 if subj discontinued <=visit 4 and > visit 3), 81mg per day for the # of days subj was in 2nd dosing interval (i.e., visit12date-visit4date if 2nd interval completed, TRTEDT-visit4date if subj discontinued <= visit 12 and > visit 4), and 54mg per day for the # of days subj was in 3rd dosing interval (i.e., TRTEDT - visit12date if subj continued after visit 12).

methods.name: Derivation Method for AGEGR1
methods.description: Character variable derived from ADSL.AGEGR1N

methods.name: Derivation Method for AGEGR1N
methods.description: AGEGR1 = 1 if AGE <65. AGEGR1 = 2 if AGE 65-80. AGEGR1 = 3 if AGE >80.

methods.name: Derivation Method for SAFFL
methods.description: Y if ITTFL='Y' and TRTSDT ne missing. N otherwise

methods.name: Derivation Method for EFFFL
methods.description: Y if SAFFL='Y AND subject has at least one record in QS for ADAS-Cog with VISITNUM>3 AND at least one record in QS for CIBIC+ with VISITNUM>3, N otherwise

methods.name: Derivation Method for COMP8FL
methods.description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=8 and ENDDT >= date of visit 8, N otherwise

methods.name: Derivation Method for COMP16FL
methods.description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=10 and ENDDT>=date of visit 10, N otherwise

methods.name: Derivation Method for COMP24FL
methods.description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=12 and ENDDT>= date of visit 12 , N otherwise

methods.name: Derivation Method for DISCONFL
methods.description: Y if DCREASCD ^= 'Completed'. Null otherwise

methods.name: Derivation Method for DSRAEFL
methods.description: Y if DCREASCD='Adverse Event'. Null otherwise

methods.name: Derivation Method for BMIBLGR1
methods.description: BMIBLGR1=Normal if . < BMIBL <25. BMIBLGR1=Overweight if 25 <=BMIBL <30. BMIBLGR1=Obese if BMIBL >=30

methods.name: Derivation Method for HEIGHTBL
methods.description: VSSTRESN when VS.VSTESTCD='HEIGHT' and VS.VISITNUM=1

methods.name: Derivation Method for WEIGHTBL
methods.description: VSSTRESN when VS.VSTESTCD='WEIGHT' and VS.VISITNUM=3

methods.name: Derivation Method for EDUCLVL
methods.description: SC.SCSTRESN where SC.SCTESTCD=YEARSEDU

methods.name: Derivation Method for DISONSDT
methods.description: MH.MHSTDTC where MHCAT='PRIMARY DIAGNOSIS' converted to SAS date

methods.name: Derivation Method for DURDIS
methods.description: number of months between VISIT1DT and DISONSET

methods.name: Derivation Method for DURDSGR1
methods.description: grouping DURDIS values as <12 and >=12

methods.name: Derivation Method for VISIT1DT
methods.description: SV.SVSTDTC when SV.VISITNUM=1, converted to SAS date

methods.name: Derivation Method for VISNUMEN
methods.description: if DS.VISITNUM=13 where DSTERM='PROTCOL COMPLETED' then VISNUMEN=12, otherwise VISNUMEN=DS.VISITNUM where DSTERM='PROTCOL COMPLETED'

methods.name: Derivation Method for DCDECOD
methods.description: DS.DSDECOD where DSCAT='DISPOSITION EVENT'

methods.name: Derivation Method for DCREASCD
methods.description: Grouping of DCDECOD values to support summarizing study completion status and reason for discontinuation

methods.name: Derivation Method for MMSETOT
methods.description: sum of QS.QSORRES values for the subject

methods.name: Derivation Method for PARAM
methods.description: PARAM="Time to First Dermatologic Event"

methods.name: Derivation Method for ADT
methods.description: if ADAE.ASTDT is not missing and occurred after TRTSDT then ADAE.ASTDT else convert ADSL.RFENDTC to a SAS numeric date

methods.name: Derivation Method for CNSR
methods.description: if ADAE.TRTEMFL ="Y" then CNSR=0, else CNSR=1

methods.name: Derivation Method for EVNTDESC
methods.description: if ADTTE.CNSR = 0 then "Dematologic Event Occured", else if ADTTE.CNSR =1 then "Study Completion Date"

methods.name: Derivation Method for SRCDOM
methods.description: The Source domain referred to in order to populate ADT (either ADAE or ADSL)

methods.name: Derivation Method for SRCVAR
methods.description: The Source variable referred to in order to populate ADT (either ASTDT or RFENDT)

methods.name: Derivation Method for SRCSEQ
methods.description: The value of ADAE.AESEQ if SRCDOM=ADAE, otherwise null.

methods.name: Derivation Method for ADT
methods.description: the date part of VS.VSDTC converted to a SAS date

methods.name: Derivation Method for AVISIT
methods.description: Derived from VS.VISIT for values to be included in a per visit analysis. AVISIT is missing for values from SDTM screening visits, unscheduled visits, and event related visits, e.g. "AMBUL ECG REMOVAL", which are not included in a per visit analysis.

methods.name: Derivation Method for ANL01FL
methods.description: ANL01FL="Y" if the value is to be included in a per visit analysis. ANL01FL is missing for values from SDTM screening visits, unscheduled visits, and event related visits, e.g. "AMBUL ECG REMOVAL"

methods.name: Derivation Method for MCHC
methods.description: Y if VISITNUM=1, null otherwise

methods.name: Derivation Method for CHOL
methods.description: Y if this ALBTRVAL is the largest for the subject in Visits 4-12 inclusive, null otherwise (if this value of ALBTRVAL occurs more than once, the first one is flagged).

methods.name: Derivation Method for _PHOS
methods.description: Y if the absolute value of this AVAL is the largest for the subject for VISITS 4-12 inclusive, null otherwise; only the first on-treatment AVAL that has absolute val equal to the max is flagged.

methods.name: Derivation Method for MCHC
methods.description: if AVAL < (0.5*LBSTNRLO) then ANRIND='L'; if LAVAL > 1.5* LBSTNRHI then ANRIND='H'; ANRIND='N' otherwise. Used for shift tables

methods.name: Derivation Method for _ANISO
methods.description: if AVAL < -1 then ANRIND='L'; if AVAL > 1 then ANRIND='H'; ANRIND='N' otherwise; null if LBBLFL=Y or AVAL=null

methods.name: Derivation Method for _ANISO
methods.description: (LBSTRESN - previous LBSTRESN)/(.5*(LBSTNRHI-LBSTNRLO)); null if LBBLFL=Y

methods.name: Derivation Method for CHOL
methods.description: ADLBC.LBSTRESN when ADLBC.ABLFL=Y

methods.name: Derivation Method for CHOL
methods.description: ADLBC.ANRIND when ADLBC.ABLFL=Y

methods.name: Derivation Method for MCV
methods.description: Y if this ALBTRVAL is the largest for the subject in Visits 4-12 inclusive, null otherwise (if this value of ALBTRVAL occurs more than once, the first one is flagged)

methods.name: Derivation Method for _ANISO
methods.description: Y if the absolute value of this AVAL is the largest for the subject for VISITS 4-12 inclusive, null otherwise; only the first on-treatment AVAL that has absolute val equal to the max is flagged

methods.name: Derivation Method for MCV
methods.description: ADLBH.ANRIND when ADLBH.ABLFL=Y

methods.name: Derivation Method for BILI
methods.description: for a given visit, if param='BILI' and r2a1hi > 1.5 then aval=1. otherwise if param='BILI' then aval=0

methods.name: Derivation Method for ALT/AST
methods.description: for a given visit, if param='ALT' or 'AST' and if either r2a1hi > 1.5 then aval=1. otherwise if param='ALT' or 'AST' then aval=0

methods.name: Derivation Method for BILHY/TRANSHY
methods.description: for a given visit, if param='BILHY' or 'TRANSHY' and if both has aval=1 then for this param then aval=1. otherwise if for a given visit, if param='BILHY' or 'TRANSHY' then aval=0.

methods.name: Derivation Method for BILI
methods.description: if R21AHI > 1.5 then set to 'Y'. If R2A1HI is not missing then set to 'N'. Else set to missing.

methods.name: Derivation Method for TRANSHY
methods.description: Set to "High to Normal" if base=1 and aval=0, set to "Normal to Normal" if base=0 and aval=0, and set to "Normal to High" if base=0 and aval=1

methods.name: Derivation Method for ACITM12
methods.description: QS.QSSTRESN where QSTESTCD=PARAMCD

methods.name: Derivation Method for ACTOT
methods.description: Sum of ADAS scores for items 1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 11, 12, 13, and 14, see SAP section 14.2 for details on adjusting for missing values.

methods.name: Derivation Method for QSSEQ
methods.description: Set QSSEQ to missing for post baseline records. Set to QS.QSSEQ where QS.VISIT=BASELINE and QS.QSTESTCD=ACTOT.

methods.name: Derivation Method for NPTOT
methods.description: QS.QSSTRESN where QSTESTCD = given PARAMCD

methods.name: Derivation Method for NPTOT
methods.description: take the mean of AVAL when PARAMCD=NPTOT from week 4 to 24.

methods.name: Derivation Method for BASE
methods.description: Set BASE to QS.QSSTRESN when QS.QSTESTCD=NPTOT and QS.QSBLFL=Y.

methods.name: Derivation Method for NPTOT
methods.description: AVAL - BASE, for post baseline records.

methods.name: Derivation Method for NPTOT
methods.description: 100* (CHG/BASE), for post baseline records.

methods.name: Derivation Method for QSSEQ
methods.description: Set QSSEQ to missing for post baseline records. Set to QS.QSSEQ where QS.VISIT=BASELINE and QS.QSTESTCD=NPTOT.
